1
00:00:03,379 --> 00:00:05,632
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

2
00:00:05,715 --> 00:00:08,343
<i>I pledged a vow to the revolution</i>

3
00:00:08,468 --> 00:00:13,473
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

4
00:00:13,556 --> 00:00:18,645
<i>I'm going to change</i>

5
00:00:27,111 --> 00:00:31,407
<i>The future that
the forbidden fruit foretells...</i>

6
00:00:31,533 --> 00:00:35,495
<i>I'm going the change</i>

7
00:00:35,578 --> 00:00:39,832
<i>The dream into reality</i>

8
00:00:42,544 --> 00:00:48,383
<i>The ending</i>

9
00:00:48,466 --> 00:00:51,719
<i>That everybody wants</i>

10
00:00:52,679 --> 00:00:54,973
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

11
00:00:55,056 --> 00:00:57,725
<i>I pledged our vow to the revolution</i>

12
00:00:57,809 --> 00:01:02,605
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

13
00:01:02,772 --> 00:01:08,027
<i>Someday I'll show you</i>

14
00:01:08,152 --> 00:01:11,322
<i>A bright and ideal</i>

15
00:01:11,406 --> 00:01:17,412
<i>World</i>

16
00:01:26,921 --> 00:01:30,008
CONFESSION

17
00:01:32,552 --> 00:01:37,307
<i>Light, another message from
the Second Kira was sent t0 Sakura TV.</i>

18
00:01:38,099 --> 00:01:39,767
<i>This time it's a video and a diary.</i>

19
00:01:40,226 --> 00:01:42,186
<i>I thought I'd tell you.</i>

20
00:01:42,729 --> 00:01:45,940
<i>A diary? He made another move?
That idiot.</i>

21
00:01:46,733 --> 00:01:48,359
<i>Can't he just sit still a while?</i>

22
00:01:52,488 --> 00:01:54,157
Did he want the diary to
be shown on TV?

23
00:01:54,657 --> 00:01:55,950
Yeah. This is it.

24
00:01:58,911 --> 00:02:02,123
<i>2006... Last year's diary?</i>

25
00:02:03,207 --> 00:02:05,460
Please take a look at the thirtieth.

26
00:02:06,586 --> 00:02:10,214
28TH SOMETHING BETTER THAN THE PZZ IS COMING CDLJT, ITS CALLED
PZX. 30TH CCDNFIRIVIED CDLJR SHINIGAIVII AT THE TOKYC) DCDIVIE

27
00:02:10,381 --> 00:02:13,843
<i>I'm pretty sure he's saying he wants
to do that on May 30...</i>

28
00:02:15,011 --> 00:02:16,888
<i>If we air this,</i>

29
00:02:16,971 --> 00:02:19,140
<i>the public will find that
that's what he plans to do.</i>

30
00:02:20,683 --> 00:02:21,726
<i>Furthermore...</i>

31
00:02:21,809 --> 00:02:24,187
<i>he can't see my Shinigami unless
he touches my notebook,</i>

32
00:02:24,270 --> 00:02:25,813
<i>so how does he plan to do that?</i>

33
00:02:26,814 --> 00:02:29,817
22ND MY FRIEND AND I SHOWED OFF
OUR NOTEBOOKS IN AOYAMA

34
00:02:31,611 --> 00:02:32,695
Hey, Rem.

35
00:02:32,987 --> 00:02:33,988
Hmm?

36
00:02:34,322 --> 00:02:37,992
Why can't I see my own lifespan
even if I have the Shinigami eyes?

37
00:02:38,076 --> 00:02:40,328
MISA AMANE

38
00:02:41,162 --> 00:02:42,955
People who have Death Notes

39
00:02:43,039 --> 00:02:45,708
only need to know the lifespan
of the people they kill.

40
00:02:46,042 --> 00:02:50,380
Just like Shinigami can't see
the lifespan of other Shinigami...

41
00:02:50,963 --> 00:02:54,300
people who hold a Death Note
can't see each other's lifespans.

42
00:02:57,595 --> 00:03:01,391
<i>May 22nd, My friend and I showed off
our notebooks in Aoyama.</i>

43
00:03:02,141 --> 00:03:05,019
<i>If "notebook" means "Death Note,"</i>

44
00:03:05,687 --> 00:03:07,522
<i>then it would only be understood
by me, Kira.</i>

45
00:03:08,481 --> 00:03:09,565
<i>And the police...</i>

46
00:03:09,982 --> 00:03:12,652
<i>will probably pay attention to
the May 30 entry which says,</i>

47
00:03:12,735 --> 00:03:16,906
<i>"We confirmed our Shinigami
at the Tokyo Dome."</i>

48
00:03:17,949 --> 00:03:22,120
<i>I'm pretty sure that the "Aoyama" part
of the message is the real message...</i>

49
00:03:22,954 --> 00:03:24,455
<i>But if that's the case...</i>

50
00:03:25,289 --> 00:03:27,417
Light, what do you think?

51
00:03:29,585 --> 00:03:31,295
<i>I shouldn't say anything carelessly.</i>

52
00:03:31,462 --> 00:03:33,631
<i>I should watch
how he approaches this...</i>

53
00:03:34,966 --> 00:03:38,344
Right now...
I can only say that he's an idiot.

54
00:03:38,803 --> 00:03:39,971
He is, isn't he?

55
00:03:40,304 --> 00:03:43,474
It's obvious that he wants to
meet Kira at the home game.

56
00:03:43,975 --> 00:03:46,686
Doesn't he understand that
if we air this there'll be a panic

57
00:03:46,811 --> 00:03:49,856
and the game will be canceled?

58
00:03:50,690 --> 00:03:52,859
To be honest, it's so stupid...

59
00:03:54,068 --> 00:03:57,405
That I'm not sure how to
deal with it...

60
00:03:59,782 --> 00:04:01,284
If the diary is broadcast,

61
00:04:01,659 --> 00:04:05,955
then we'll have to announce that
the game on the 30th is canceled.

62
00:04:06,664 --> 00:04:10,168
But if we don't, the Second Kira
won't make a move.

63
00:04:10,585 --> 00:04:12,420
But if he gets angry that
we cancelled the game,

64
00:04:12,503 --> 00:04:13,629
there's no telling what he'll do...

65
00:04:14,380 --> 00:04:15,673
That's all right.

66
00:04:16,215 --> 00:04:19,510
The Second Kira
seems to revere Kira.

67
00:04:20,052 --> 00:04:23,639
He promised the Kira we created,
that he'd refrain from killing excessively.

68
00:04:23,723 --> 00:04:25,183
We can believe that.

69
00:04:26,517 --> 00:04:30,813
Anyway, we'll air the diary and announce
the cancellation of the game...

70
00:04:31,314 --> 00:04:34,859
And also announce that we're going
to close off and inspect all roads

71
00:04:35,109 --> 00:04:37,195
around the Tokyo Dome.

72
00:04:37,862 --> 00:04:41,032
Furthermore, our "own" Kira
will respond with,

73
00:04:41,365 --> 00:04:44,619
"Understood. Let's meet."

74
00:04:44,869 --> 00:04:47,872
You don't really think that they would
go there even

75
00:04:47,955 --> 00:04:49,916
if we're inspecting the roads
around the dome, do you?

76
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:54,879
I don't think that the real Kira will go,
but I'm not sure about the Second Kira.

77
00:04:55,546 --> 00:04:57,381
I can't tell how stupid he is.

78
00:04:58,257 --> 00:04:59,300
Also...

79
00:04:59,383 --> 00:05:02,386
Assuming that he isn't
as stupid as we think he is...

80
00:05:02,845 --> 00:05:06,557
I'll try to see if there might
be another message within this diary.

81
00:05:09,352 --> 00:05:11,312
If there is a code that
only people

82
00:05:11,395 --> 00:05:16,317
who have the so-called Shinigami power
can understand, I can't decode it.

83
00:05:17,276 --> 00:05:22,240
But we should thoroughly check out
the places listed in the diary.

84
00:05:23,533 --> 00:05:26,494
The 22nd, he's meeting
a friend in Aoyama.

85
00:05:27,245 --> 00:05:30,414
The 24th, he's meeting
a friend in Shibuya.

86
00:05:31,332 --> 00:05:33,209
We have to prepare for the possibility
that our efforts will be fruitless.

87
00:05:33,292 --> 00:05:35,837
We also have to be wary of people waiting
around with notebooks in Aoyama,

88
00:05:36,045 --> 00:05:39,382
and people lurking in
clothing stores in Shibuya.

89
00:05:41,050 --> 00:05:42,260
<i>It's as I thought...</i>

90
00:05:42,885 --> 00:05:47,265
<i>If the fake Kira is caught,
I'll have t0 obtain his notebook...</i>

91
00:05:48,432 --> 00:05:51,853
<i>In the worst case scenario,
I may have to kill everyone there.</i>

92
00:05:52,895 --> 00:05:57,942
All we can do is place more surveillance
cameras in Aoyama and Shibuya

93
00:05:58,276 --> 00:06:02,113
and station undercover officers
on the stated dates.

94
00:06:02,864 --> 00:06:06,742
Then I'll go to Aoyama and
Shibuya since I'd fit right in.

95
00:06:07,952 --> 00:06:08,953
I'll go too.

96
00:06:09,203 --> 00:06:10,204
Light...

97
00:06:10,454 --> 00:06:14,876
It's all right, Dad. I go to
Aoyama and Shibuya occasionally.

98
00:06:15,418 --> 00:06:19,630
And I'd be the one who'd look
most natural hanging outwith Mr. Matsui.

99
00:06:20,464 --> 00:06:24,427
And the only person the Second Kira
is interested in is Kira.

100
00:06:28,180 --> 00:06:32,310
So Mr. Matsui, I'll talk to you tomorrow
about going to Aoyama and Shibuya.

101
00:06:32,643 --> 00:06:35,187
All right, Light. Be careful.

102
00:06:45,156 --> 00:06:47,658
<i>This always happens as soon
as I go out and turn on my phone...</i>

103
00:06:48,534 --> 00:06:49,535
Yes?

104
00:06:49,744 --> 00:06:54,832
<i>This is Ryuzaki. Please be sure
to keep an eye on Light.</i>

105
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:57,084
<i>Please keep this a secret.</i>

106
00:06:57,877 --> 00:07:00,338
Y-Yes... I understand...

107
00:07:02,423 --> 00:07:04,467
<i>As long as there's still
a small percentage of doubt,</i>

108
00:07:04,550 --> 00:07:07,219
<i>we still have
to suspect him, eh?</i>

109
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:10,473
I'm home.

110
00:07:10,681 --> 00:07:12,808
Light, you're late today.

111
00:07:12,934 --> 00:07:13,976
Yeah...

112
00:07:14,685 --> 00:07:16,187
<i>I'm supposed to keep the fact</i>

113
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:18,022
<i>that I'm helping with
the investigation a secret...</i>

114
00:07:18,731 --> 00:07:20,942
Yeah, I have a girlfriend now...

115
00:07:21,734 --> 00:07:23,694
<i>'</i> Oh, my.
- What?!

116
00:07:23,903 --> 00:07:26,113
Light has a girlfriend? Wow!

117
00:07:26,697 --> 00:07:29,408
Hey, hey, I'm an 18-year-old
college student...

118
00:07:29,992 --> 00:07:31,494
Of course, I have one.

119
00:07:32,244 --> 00:07:33,245
Good luck to you too, Sayu.

120
00:07:33,621 --> 00:07:36,499
Huh? I-| don't need
anything like that yet...

121
00:07:36,916 --> 00:07:38,459
Light, what about dinner?

122
00:07:39,085 --> 00:07:41,295
I got room service at the hotel.

123
00:07:41,545 --> 00:07:44,382
Did you just say hotel?!

124
00:07:44,674 --> 00:07:47,385
What was that?! What was that?!
So scandalous!

125
00:07:48,970 --> 00:07:51,806
All right, Ryuk...
I have something to ask you.

126
00:07:52,306 --> 00:07:54,016
Oh... I thought so.

127
00:07:54,725 --> 00:07:56,560
Answer me if you can.

128
00:07:57,395 --> 00:08:01,482
Can Shinigami who come to
the human world talk to each other?

129
00:08:02,066 --> 00:08:03,109
It's hard to say...

130
00:08:03,609 --> 00:08:06,821
If I'm attached to a human,
I think that's against the rules

131
00:08:06,904 --> 00:08:09,824
unless I have the permission
of the person I'm attached to.

132
00:08:10,408 --> 00:08:12,451
We don't have a code
against that, so I guess...

133
00:08:12,618 --> 00:08:15,871
another Shinigami might
start talking to me.

134
00:08:16,831 --> 00:08:19,000
So does that mean if
Fake Kira's Shinigami sees you,

135
00:08:19,083 --> 00:08:23,754
there's a chance that
he'll tell the Fake Kira that I'm Kira?

136
00:08:24,672 --> 00:08:27,341
That's usually not done,
but it depends on their personality.

137
00:08:28,050 --> 00:08:32,513
So I can just assume that
you'll act how you usually do, right?

138
00:08:32,847 --> 00:08:37,810
Yeah. Even if I see someone
with a Shinigami, I won't tell you.

139
00:08:38,602 --> 00:08:41,105
Well, I agree with your stance.

140
00:08:41,522 --> 00:08:42,523
Thanks.

141
00:08:43,816 --> 00:08:44,817
Hmm?

142
00:08:45,109 --> 00:08:48,320
So, Fake Kira... Have you thought
this out this far?

143
00:08:48,863 --> 00:08:49,864
What's wrong?

144
00:08:50,489 --> 00:08:51,991
Aoyama is pretty big.

145
00:08:52,616 --> 00:08:56,162
I was searching for ways we
could find each other, but...

146
00:08:56,746 --> 00:09:01,542
On the 22nd, there is an event at
a club called the Note Blue in Aoyama...

147
00:09:02,043 --> 00:09:05,963
<i>A0</i> means "Blue"...
And "note"...

148
00:09:07,631 --> 00:09:09,133
That's pretty elaborate...

149
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:11,927
He might be smarter than I thought...

150
00:09:12,636 --> 00:09:16,223
That means I need to be
more careful, but...

151
00:09:16,682 --> 00:09:20,269
right now, this Note Blue
is worth checking out.

152
00:09:20,936 --> 00:09:25,483
But you don't want him to
know that you're Kira, right?

153
00:09:34,075 --> 00:09:36,535
Uh... Light?

154
00:09:36,994 --> 00:09:38,079
What's going on?

155
00:09:38,704 --> 00:09:40,539
These are my friends from school.

156
00:09:42,208 --> 00:09:43,250
P-Pleased to meet you...

157
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:45,127
This is my cousin Taro.

158
00:09:45,669 --> 00:09:47,004
It's his first time in Tokyo

159
00:09:47,129 --> 00:09:50,800
and he said he wanted to go have
some fun in Aoyama and Roppongi.

160
00:09:51,383 --> 00:09:52,551
I'll be counting on you guys!

161
00:09:52,802 --> 00:09:55,387
He's also looking for a girlfriend.

162
00:09:55,679 --> 00:09:57,389
Does anyone want to volunteer?

163
00:09:58,182 --> 00:09:59,517
Hey, Light...

164
00:10:02,269 --> 00:10:03,729
<i>I'm impressed, Light.</i>

165
00:10:04,105 --> 00:10:05,564
<i>No one would ever suspect</i>

166
00:10:05,648 --> 00:10:08,234
<i>a police officer among
a group of kids.</i>

167
00:10:12,363 --> 00:10:14,156
<i>Even if Ryuk is spotted,</i>

168
00:10:14,615 --> 00:10:18,452
<i>no one could tell who he's attached to
if I'm with this many people.</i>

169
00:10:18,911 --> 00:10:21,539
<i>It's also defense against
L's surveillance cameras...</i>

170
00:10:22,123 --> 00:10:24,083
<i>And it's not a bad way
to investigate.</i>

171
00:10:24,875 --> 00:10:29,171
<i>I just have to watch the entrance
of the Note Blue when it opens..</i>

172
00:10:37,555 --> 00:10:38,597
Found him!

173
00:10:45,563 --> 00:10:48,566
<i>Is it read. . . Tsuki [Moon]. . . Yagami?</i>

174
00:10:48,983 --> 00:10:51,068
<i>He's the only one whose
lifespan I can't see.</i>

175
00:10:51,610 --> 00:10:53,320
LIGHT YAGAMI

176
00:10:53,737 --> 00:10:56,824
<i>I never thought I would
find him so easily.</i>

177
00:11:03,038 --> 00:11:04,665
All right, Rem. Let's go home.

178
00:11:05,082 --> 00:11:07,918
What? You just found him.
Is that good enough?

179
00:11:08,586 --> 00:11:12,590
I can't just greet him by saying,
"Mr. Kira...I'm pleased to meet you,"

180
00:11:12,673 --> 00:11:14,592
with all these people around.

181
00:11:15,676 --> 00:11:18,762
I know his name.
I can look him up later.

182
00:11:20,014 --> 00:11:21,599
After all, it's such a unique name.

183
00:11:36,572 --> 00:11:39,700
YAGAIVII, LIGHT BIRTHDATE FEBRUARY 28, 1989
HEIGHT 179CM VVEIGHT 54KG BLOOD TYPE A

184
00:11:40,034 --> 00:11:41,619
That's kind of dreamy!

185
00:11:42,077 --> 00:11:44,705
Anyways,
Light Yagami is impressive...

186
00:11:45,289 --> 00:11:46,874
He won the national tennis competition

187
00:11:46,957 --> 00:11:49,376
when he was in his second and
third year of middle school.

188
00:11:49,627 --> 00:11:51,962
He gave an address as
the freshman representative

189
00:11:52,046 --> 00:11:54,256
at this year's entrance ceremony
at To-oh University...

190
00:11:55,007 --> 00:11:56,383
There's no picture of him,

191
00:11:56,467 --> 00:11:58,844
but there can't be anyone else
with a name like this.

192
00:11:59,887 --> 00:12:03,265
<i>Who would have thought that Kira
would be so young and cool!</i>

193
00:12:04,016 --> 00:12:05,976
<i>He's better than I ever imagined.</i>

194
00:12:07,019 --> 00:12:09,063
There are so many places that will
just go and sell your personal records.

195
00:12:09,396 --> 00:12:11,106
The world is so twisted, isn't it?

196
00:12:11,357 --> 00:12:12,650
I even know his address now!

197
00:12:14,652 --> 00:12:15,986
So in the end...

198
00:12:16,278 --> 00:12:17,905
There isn't a trace of anything
happening in Aoyama

199
00:12:17,988 --> 00:12:22,368
on the 22nd and Shibuya on the 24th.

200
00:12:22,743 --> 00:12:25,162
The only place left is
the Dome on the 30th...

201
00:12:26,413 --> 00:12:29,959
<i>I didn't see anyone who could
be the Fake Kira at Note Blue.</i>

202
00:12:30,626 --> 00:12:32,378
<i>Could he really be going
to the Dome?</i>

203
00:12:33,879 --> 00:12:36,507
<i>Ryuzaki, Sakura TV just received</i>

204
00:12:36,674 --> 00:12:38,842
<i>another message
from the Second Kira.</i>

205
00:12:40,010 --> 00:12:41,845
<i>It's postmarked. . .on the 23rd.</i>

206
00:12:44,181 --> 00:12:46,225
<i>I have found Kira.</i>

207
00:12:46,767 --> 00:12:48,352
<i>To all of the people at
the television station</i>

208
00:12:48,435 --> 00:12:51,230
<i>and the police, thank you very much.</i>

209
00:12:52,856 --> 00:12:54,358
<i>I-It can't be-!</i>

210
00:12:54,942 --> 00:12:56,902
<i>Where? In Aoyama?</i>

211
00:12:57,444 --> 00:13:00,322
<i>Did his Shinigami find
Ryuk and tell him?</i>

212
00:13:01,115 --> 00:13:04,451
<i>No. . . There is no Wa y that he could
tell who Ryuk was attached t0.</i>

213
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:07,371
<i>I made sure that no one
was following me...</i>

214
00:13:08,205 --> 00:13:12,710
<i>If this is true, the only thing that
corresponds to this tape</i>

215
00:13:12,793 --> 00:13:15,629
<i>being mailed on the 23rd
is the 22nd in Aoyama</i>

216
00:13:16,505 --> 00:13:18,465
<i>Matsuda and Light Yagami are
the only ones</i>

217
00:13:18,549 --> 00:13:20,509
<i>from this investigation
who went to Aoyama.</i>

218
00:13:21,135 --> 00:13:22,761
<i>Is Light really Kira-?</i>

219
00:13:23,637 --> 00:13:25,597
<i>But we don't have absolute proof
this happened in Aoyama.</i>

220
00:13:26,390 --> 00:13:28,183
He found him?
That's not good.

221
00:13:28,475 --> 00:13:32,688
Yes... It means that the Second Kira
and Kira have teamed up...

222
00:13:33,188 --> 00:13:35,566
We're still not sure
if they've teamed up.

223
00:13:36,483 --> 00:13:39,028
The Second Kira is only saying
that he found him.

224
00:13:39,778 --> 00:13:41,530
He may not have contacted him yet.

225
00:13:43,365 --> 00:13:44,908
Since we've come to this point...

226
00:13:46,910 --> 00:13:50,914
the police will have to send
a message to the Second Kira...

227
00:13:51,665 --> 00:13:52,750
Send a message?

228
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:57,588
Yes. The police will have to reach out
to the Second Kira

229
00:13:57,963 --> 00:14:00,924
and offer him a deal in
exchange for Kira's name.

230
00:14:03,260 --> 00:14:06,138
Isn't this a really bad turn
of events?

231
00:14:06,555 --> 00:14:07,681
<i>This isn't good...</i>

232
00:14:08,098 --> 00:14:10,726
<i>I don't know how
the Fake Kira would react...</i>

233
00:14:11,435 --> 00:14:14,229
<i>But I have no reason to stop this...</i>

234
00:14:15,898 --> 00:14:20,903
<i>If Kira doesn't know who you are yet,
there is still time.</i>

235
00:14:21,362 --> 00:14:24,406
<i>Don't approach Kira out of curiosity.</i>

236
00:14:25,115 --> 00:14:28,118
<i>Kira will kill you if you contact him.</i>

237
00:14:28,702 --> 00:14:29,995
<i>He'll just use you.</i>

238
00:14:30,788 --> 00:14:35,000
<i>What you can do is reconsider
the value of human life,</i>

239
00:14:35,501 --> 00:14:38,962
<i>and atone for your crimes by
giving us information on Kira,</i>

240
00:14:39,254 --> 00:14:42,174
<i>and save the people of the world
from Kira's reign of terror.</i>

241
00:14:45,844 --> 00:14:46,929
Where are you going?

242
00:14:47,638 --> 00:14:48,889
I'm going to introduce myself.

243
00:14:50,808 --> 00:14:52,142
<i>Oh, to him...</i>

244
00:14:53,018 --> 00:14:54,812
Oh, I wonder if it's your father.

245
00:14:55,062 --> 00:14:56,105
Coming...

246
00:14:58,023 --> 00:14:59,400
Welcome home-!

247
00:15:00,776 --> 00:15:01,777
Huh?

248
00:15:02,528 --> 00:15:05,114
Good evening.
My name is Misa Amane.

249
00:15:05,948 --> 00:15:09,743
I came to give Light an important
notebook he left at the university...

250
00:15:09,827 --> 00:15:12,037
C-Could you wait for a second?

251
00:15:13,747 --> 00:15:15,165
Light-!

252
00:15:16,375 --> 00:15:18,168
<i>Notebook-?! Could it be-?</i>

253
00:15:32,933 --> 00:15:34,143
Pleased to meet you...

254
00:15:34,685 --> 00:15:35,853
My name is Misa Amane.

255
00:15:36,687 --> 00:15:39,690
I thought you might be worried
if you were watching TV...

256
00:15:40,065 --> 00:15:41,942
I just couldn't take it any more...

257
00:15:42,276 --> 00:15:43,402
This notebook...

258
00:15:45,028 --> 00:15:46,113
<i>A Death Note...</i>

259
00:15:53,704 --> 00:15:54,872
<i>A Shinigami-!</i>

260
00:15:55,873 --> 00:15:56,915
<i>She's the Fake Kira...</i>

261
00:15:59,168 --> 00:16:00,210
Come on in.

262
00:16:01,211 --> 00:16:03,380
Huh? Is it all right-?
I'm so happy.

263
00:16:04,214 --> 00:16:06,717
Mom, she came all this way
to return my notebook to me.

264
00:16:07,134 --> 00:16:08,218
Could you make us some tea
or something?

265
00:16:08,427 --> 00:16:09,887
L-| suppose I should.

266
00:16:12,264 --> 00:16:13,432
She's the one
I was telling you about.

267
00:16:19,313 --> 00:16:20,314
Have a seat.

268
00:16:21,356 --> 00:16:23,066
T-Thank you.

269
00:16:33,952 --> 00:16:34,953
How did you find me?

270
00:16:35,829 --> 00:16:39,416
Oh... I thought so. You didn't do
the deal for the eyes, did you?

271
00:16:41,001 --> 00:16:42,419
When you have the Shinigami eyes,

272
00:16:42,753 --> 00:16:46,757
you can see a person's
lifespan and age. But...

273
00:16:46,924 --> 00:16:50,093
you cannot see the lifespan
of someone who has a Death Note.

274
00:16:52,471 --> 00:16:56,558
Well... I didn't know that detail...

275
00:16:57,267 --> 00:16:59,436
Okay, I understand that, but...

276
00:17:00,103 --> 00:17:02,481
What would happen if you were
caught by the police

277
00:17:02,648 --> 00:17:04,566
and Kira's secret was discovered-?

278
00:17:05,108 --> 00:17:06,109
It's all right...

279
00:17:06,568 --> 00:17:12,658
I wasn't caught and if I continue
to do as you say, I won't be. Right?

280
00:17:13,450 --> 00:17:15,452
And I will see L's name...

281
00:17:16,453 --> 00:17:18,121
I will become your eyes...

282
00:17:19,331 --> 00:17:20,290
So...

283
00:17:23,043 --> 00:17:24,086
So'?

284
00:17:25,254 --> 00:17:26,505
Please make me your girlfriend!

285
00:17:28,966 --> 00:17:29,967
Girlfriend-?

286
00:17:30,968 --> 00:17:31,969
Yes...

287
00:17:33,804 --> 00:17:36,974
<i>If I'm not careful with her,
she might kill me...</i>

288
00:17:37,641 --> 00:17:38,684
<i>But...</i>

289
00:17:39,309 --> 00:17:40,394
That's impossible.

290
00:17:40,477 --> 00:17:45,107
There were three times
the usual number of surveillance cameras.

291
00:17:45,524 --> 00:17:50,821
Anyone in Aoyama would have
been caught on camera. Including me.

292
00:17:51,697 --> 00:17:53,657
If we get together after that...

293
00:17:54,283 --> 00:17:56,827
Even being together here isn't good.

294
00:17:57,619 --> 00:17:58,996
Try to understand.

295
00:17:59,663 --> 00:18:03,166
This is a picture of me
when I went to Aoyama.

296
00:18:06,128 --> 00:18:08,422
I'm sure no one would
recognize her like this.

297
00:18:08,839 --> 00:18:10,299
So what about your fingerprints?

298
00:18:10,882 --> 00:18:13,510
The tapes you sent to
the television station...

299
00:18:13,594 --> 00:18:15,512
all have the same fingerprints.

300
00:18:15,846 --> 00:18:17,639
Those aren't my fingerprints.

301
00:18:18,015 --> 00:18:20,684
<i>I did</i> put some thought
into my actions.

302
00:18:21,518 --> 00:18:23,645
A little while back I lived
in the Kansai region.

303
00:18:24,021 --> 00:18:25,981
I had a friend who was into the occult.

304
00:18:26,732 --> 00:18:29,359
When I told her we should
make fake ghost videos and

305
00:18:29,484 --> 00:18:32,279
send it to several TV shows,

306
00:18:32,446 --> 00:18:34,197
she agreed to help me.

307
00:18:34,990 --> 00:18:37,159
I had her dub ten tapes and

308
00:18:37,326 --> 00:18:40,871
I made sure not to leave
any fingerprints.

309
00:18:41,079 --> 00:18:42,831
I took those video tapes,

310
00:18:42,914 --> 00:18:44,625
added a graphic,
and added sound.

311
00:18:45,542 --> 00:18:48,045
And what is that friend doing now?

312
00:18:48,587 --> 00:18:51,798
If you want me to kill her,
I'll kill her right now!

313
00:18:54,217 --> 00:18:55,969
If you really...
don't believe me...

314
00:18:56,845 --> 00:18:59,848
You can hold on to my Death Note.

315
00:19:00,474 --> 00:19:03,435
You're just holding on to it,
so I'll still have ownership and

316
00:19:03,518 --> 00:19:05,562
I'll still have my eyes.

317
00:19:06,104 --> 00:19:07,522
Isn't that right, Rem?

318
00:19:08,231 --> 00:19:09,232
Indeed.

319
00:19:11,109 --> 00:19:13,320
Now there's no way
I can kill you.

320
00:19:13,904 --> 00:19:17,199
If I'm of no use, you can kill me.

321
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:19,951
<i>Why would she go this far?</i>

322
00:19:21,370 --> 00:19:24,331
But you might have removed
several pages from the Death Note.

323
00:19:24,414 --> 00:19:26,249
You could be hiding them somewhere.

324
00:19:27,626 --> 00:19:29,252
Why are you so suspicious of me?!

325
00:19:29,878 --> 00:19:32,714
I don't care if you use me!

326
00:19:33,507 --> 00:19:34,549
Believe me.

327
00:19:35,842 --> 00:19:37,427
How can you say that?

328
00:19:39,930 --> 00:19:41,264
Exactly one year ago,

329
00:19:41,348 --> 00:19:46,228
my parents were killed by
a burglar right before my eyes.

330
00:19:47,354 --> 00:19:49,064
I couldn't forgive him...

331
00:19:49,940 --> 00:19:53,944
the trial was drawn-out and some people
started saying he was falsely accused...

332
00:19:55,237 --> 00:19:58,949
That's when Kira punished him...

333
00:19:59,991 --> 00:20:03,203
Kira...means everything to me.

334
00:20:05,831 --> 00:20:09,835
I just... I just wanted to
meet you so badly!

335
00:20:10,419 --> 00:20:12,045
I wanted to thank you.

336
00:20:16,299 --> 00:20:20,679
<i>All these irrational methods
just to meet Kira...</i>

337
00:20:21,096 --> 00:20:23,140
<i>But at least she can get
around surveillance cameras</i>

338
00:20:23,223 --> 00:20:26,560
<i>and keep her fingerprints
off the evidence.</i>

339
00:20:26,977 --> 00:20:28,812
<i>She's not as stupid as I thought...</i>

340
00:20:29,521 --> 00:20:32,649
<i>She even says that she'll obey me...</i>

341
00:20:53,128 --> 00:20:54,212
I understand...

342
00:20:54,588 --> 00:20:57,340
I can't be your boyfriend,
but I can play the part...

343
00:20:58,341 --> 00:21:03,722
Those eyes you gave up half of
your life for, to meet me and to help me,

344
00:21:03,805 --> 00:21:05,557
will be a valuable weapon.

345
00:21:07,350 --> 00:21:11,480
Thank you...
I'll work hard to make you love me.

346
00:21:24,117 --> 00:21:28,538
TO BE CONTINUED

347
00:21:28,872 --> 00:21:33,835
<i>I dreamed a dream
that no one could see,</i>

348
00:21:33,919 --> 00:21:39,216
<i>I threw away everything
that I didn't need</i>

349
00:21:39,299 --> 00:21:42,761
<i>I'm holding these feelings</i>

350
00:21:42,844 --> 00:21:48,225
<i>That I can't give up in my heart</i>

351
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:54,606
<i>Even if my feet fall victim
to the shackles of sacrifice</i>

352
00:21:54,689 --> 00:21:59,194
<i>In between reality and my ideal</i>

353
00:21:59,986 --> 00:22:04,866
<i>I can't hold back
the flooding impulses</i>

354
00:22:05,116 --> 00:22:08,662
<i>Because I have a strong desire</i>

355
00:22:08,745 --> 00:22:12,332
<i>To accomplish</i>

356
00:22:12,958 --> 00:22:17,546
<i>[deceit] [fear] [vanity] [melancholy]</i>

357
00:22:17,754 --> 00:22:23,260
<i>I'm not weak enough to believe</i>

358
00:22:23,343 --> 00:22:28,306
<i>Any of these negative perceptions</i>

359
00:22:28,765 --> 00:22:34,104
<i>I'm a trickster
who doesn't know solitude</i>

360
00:22:38,483 --> 00:22:40,485
PREVIEW

361
00:22:40,485 --> 00:22:40,944
Yeah, Ryuzaki,

362
00:22:40,986 --> 00:22:44,656
I consider you a friend too.
We have so much in common.

363
00:22:45,699 --> 00:22:47,909
It's been lonely since you've been
taking breaks from school.

364
00:22:48,952 --> 00:22:50,912
I'd like to play tennis
with you again.

365
00:22:51,413 --> 00:22:53,498
NEXT EPISODE: FRIEND

